00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:03,820 --> 00:01:05,600
(Xue Tian, young master of the Xue family)
(What if the Commander finds out?)

4
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,740
(Don't worry, Young Master.)

5
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,780
(Young Lady left the country
when she was twelve.)

6
00:01:08,900 --> 00:01:10,180
(Other than the Xue family,)

7
00:01:10,340 --> 00:01:11,980
(no one knows what she looks like.)

8
00:01:13,220 --> 00:01:16,139
I heard the Xue family's young lady
went abroad at twelve.

9
00:01:16,140 --> 00:01:18,540
Who would've thought
she'd be such a beauty?

10
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:21,019
The Commander of Yancheng
and the Xue family's heiress,

11
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:22,700
what a perfect match.

12
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:25,060
It's just a deal of power and money.

13
00:01:25,100 --> 00:01:26,579
The Xue family gains protection,

14
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:28,059
and the Commander gains wealth.

15
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,499
A fair trade for both sides.

16
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,660
Be careful.

17
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,739
(Li Shuche)
I heard Commander-in-Chief Li arranged the match.

18
00:01:32,740 --> 00:01:34,160
(Commander-in-Chief of Yancheng)
He's here today too.

19
00:01:34,380 --> 00:01:36,860
Isn't he just using this
to line his own pockets?

20
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:23,100
Darling,

21
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:25,740
have we met before?

22
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:30,660
I think you feel the same way I do.

23
00:02:39,140 --> 00:02:40,540
Gu Nianchi,

24
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,379
are you willing

25
00:02:42,380 --> 00:02:45,339
to take this woman as your wife

26
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:47,260
and enter into marriage with her?

27
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,899
Whether in

28
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:49,940
sickness,

29
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:51,219
health,

30
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:52,259
poverty,

31
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:53,299
or wealth,

32
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:55,220
will you stay by her side
and never leave her?

33
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:01,580
I do.

34
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:05,899
Xue Wan,

35
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:08,099
are you willing to marry this man

36
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:09,500
and become husband and wife?

37
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:13,379
Whether through sickness,
hardship, poverty, or wealth,

38
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:16,340
will you stay by his side
and never leave him?

39
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:28,060
I will...

40
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:31,540
Nobody move!

41
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:41,720
Protect Commander-in-Chief!
Protect the Commander and Madam!

42
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,590
Don't move!

43
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:49,940
Move aside!

44
00:03:56,020 --> 00:03:56,940
Gu Nianchi,

45
00:03:57,580 --> 00:03:59,100
move again and I'll kill him!

46
00:04:03,460 --> 00:04:04,940
Nianchi, save me!

47
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,860
Gu Nianchi, are you out of your mind?

48
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:24,460
Commander-in-Chief.

49
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,620
I did it to save you.

50
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:27,499
You...

51
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,459
Lieutenant Li.

52
00:04:28,460 --> 00:04:29,140
Yes, sir!

53
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,740
Escort Commander-in-Chief Li out.

54
00:04:31,740 --> 00:04:32,540
Commander-in-Chief.

55
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:37,460
Gu Nianchi,

56
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,140
I'll fight you to the death!

57
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:54,860
You?

58
00:04:55,740 --> 00:04:57,540
You can't even use a gun.

59
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:00,940
If only you'd shot me dead.

60
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:04,900
Now you've ruined my wedding.

61
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,340
I'll teach you how to shoot.

62
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:12,739
Gu Nianchi,

63
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:14,740
you'll regret this...

64
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,660
Darling, sorry for frightening you.

65
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:08,940
You're the Commander of a city.

66
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,100
A scene like this

67
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:12,220
is nothing unusual.

68
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,180
I'll have someone escort you back first.

69
00:06:15,940 --> 00:06:17,340
I need to handle some business.

70
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:18,780
See you later.

71
00:06:20,780 --> 00:06:21,660
Alright.

72
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:30,760
(Commander's Residence)

73
00:06:47,060 --> 00:06:48,220
(Gu Nianchi,)

74
00:06:48,820 --> 00:06:50,420
(I prepared poisoned wine for you.)

75
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,300
(We'll leave this world together.)

76
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:55,040
(That way, the Xue family
won't be implicated because of me.)

77
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:58,580
(And everything between us
will finally come to an end.)

78
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,880
(Xinran, Xue family's dowry maid)

79
00:07:41,820 --> 00:07:43,740
We're both dowry maids.

80
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,220
Why are you the one
marrying in Young Lady's place?

81
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:54,459
I heard

82
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:56,740
everyone in your family
died because of you.

83
00:07:56,780 --> 00:08:00,220
A jinx like you still dreams of marrying
into a powerful family?

84
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:07,140
I'm already alone anyway.

85
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:09,820
If they find out I'm an impostor,
the worst that can happen is death.

86
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:10,900
But you...

87
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:13,219
You helped cover up the bride swap.

88
00:08:13,220 --> 00:08:14,820
That's a crime punishable by death too.

89
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,799
Are you really willing
to risk your life with me?

90
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:17,699
You...

91
00:08:17,700 --> 00:08:19,660
If you don't want to die, then behave yourself.

92
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,300
Commander.

93
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,340
You're back.

94
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:46,140
(That voice...)

95
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:47,820
(It sounds so familiar.)

96
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:57,360
You had quite a fright today, darling.

97
00:08:58,660 --> 00:09:00,500
I'm already part
of the Commander's household.

98
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:02,700
Something like this doesn't bother me.

99
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:24,220
Oh.

100
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:24,980
Good.

101
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:27,259
Then get some rest early.

102
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,900
After all, tonight is our wedding night.

103
00:09:29,460 --> 00:09:30,740
No matter what,

104
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:32,620
we should at least
share a wedding toast.

105
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:39,060
You studied abroad,
yet you still care about these customs?

106
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:41,460
It's not the customs I care about.

107
00:09:42,180 --> 00:09:43,780
It's you, Commander.

108
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:17,940
A wedding toast

109
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:19,780
is meant to be shared together.

110
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,260
Alright.

111
00:10:54,540 --> 00:10:55,460
We've finished the wine.

112
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:58,120
I still have matters to attend to.
I'll leave first.

113
00:10:58,140 --> 00:10:59,180
Gu Nianchi,

114
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,540
after killing so many people today,

115
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:05,220
Have you ever felt
even a trace of guilt?

116
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,700
Why would I?

117
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:13,380
True.

118
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,620
If you were capable of feeling guilty,

119
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,260
you wouldn't have
so much blood on your hands.

120
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,300
Get some rest.

121
00:11:33,220 --> 00:11:35,300
You take the bed tonight.
I'll sleep in the study.

122
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:39,900
What's wrong?

123
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:44,300
Are you alright?

124
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:54,620
(The poison should
be taking effect by now.)

125
00:11:55,100 --> 00:11:56,100
(But...)

126
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:58,100
(Why is he fine?)

127
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:43,499
What happened last night?

128
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,340
Why can't I remember anything?

129
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:23,340
Why is my wife up so late?

130
00:13:25,220 --> 00:13:27,020
Did last night

131
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:29,780
tire you out?

132
00:13:30,660 --> 00:13:31,780
Last night, we...

133
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,740
You don't remember?

134
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:42,860
Then let me refresh your memory.

135
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:52,660
Looks like you do remember.

136
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:54,540
Last night,

137
00:13:55,220 --> 00:13:58,860
you held a knife to me just like this.

138
00:14:27,980 --> 00:14:28,940
Tell me.

139
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:31,980
Why did you try to kill me?

140
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:36,780
I just wanted
to make things more exciting.

141
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:38,300
Didn't you enjoy it, Commander?

142
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:41,780
The wine was already strong enough.

143
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,900
Did you really need this too?

144
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:47,020
Then what do you enjoy?

145
00:14:47,460 --> 00:14:49,100
I'll do whatever you like.

146
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:57,810
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

147
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:04,440
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

148
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:08,520
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

149
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:11,870
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

150
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:17,160
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

151
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:23,470
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

152
00:15:24,530 --> 00:15:30,130
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

153
00:15:30,670 --> 00:15:34,050
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

154
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:37,249
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

155
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:42,389
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

156
00:15:42,390 --> 00:15:46,709
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

157
00:15:46,710 --> 00:15:49,289
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

158
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:51,569
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

159
00:15:51,570 --> 00:15:55,119
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

160
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:59,649
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

161
00:15:59,650 --> 00:16:02,180
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

162
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,269
♪Still I walk into♪

163
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:07,869
♪The trap you set without regret♪

164
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:11,919
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

165
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:14,499
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

166
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,659
♪A stand in can never cross♪

167
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:20,099
♪The shortest distance between us♪

168
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:25,070
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

169
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:29,900
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

170
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,249
♪A substitute♪

171
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:39,250
♪Needs no reason♪

